<br>
I have to say, nicely done to you mages that can solo this because honestly at 58, it'd be hella hard without FD... I don't know how many imp's the mage epic can handle at one time, if you can take two at once then it's cake... for me I needed the 59 pet before I could even consider this camp.<br>
<br>
All the pulls I do by simply walking into aggro radius, but even at 60 sometimes I get 2.. even when I'm being careful timing the wanderers.. it just happens some times.<br>
<br>
This isn't the most necro friendly camp since the mobs are practically immune to fire, but once I get my way back to the efreeti spawn I can stay here all day no worries. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubandose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bandose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 12:09:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=393.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> hehe...Wifey (60 druid) and I have had several instances doing efreeti/imp camp where were somehow aggro 3 at a time.  It was doable, but you have to be good at /pet back off and /pet attack to keep the aggro on the pet from all the mobs and only nuke those who have had time to get aggro secured on the pet.  Also, make sure no mob that's being beaten on by the pet has a damage shield.  Those lava elementals have a nasty DS.  Now that druids have that incredible heal, I'll boldly take on 4 or 5 and not immediately start hitting gate.<br>
<br>
I haven't really had call to check the aggro caused by the new heal, but we've used it half a dozen times, and it usually completely healed the pet, and it never pulled aggro from the pet to the druid.<br>
<br>
As for truely holding this camp though, I'd strongly recommend you keep the 3 spots outside the efreeti cave clear as well as the 1 roamer, 1 non-efreeti mob that seems stationed to the left as you enter the area, and the efreeti himself.  There are also, I believe, 2 other roamers that come into range if you wait outside the efreeti cave, but unless you just can't handle it, I strongly recommend you take those as well.  This will occasionally mean 2 at once, but should never mean getting efreeti and another.  I also can't stress enough about buffing your resists and HP.  The efreeti has a nasty nuke if it lands full.<br>
<br>
Also, best tactic I've found, once you have all the non-efreeti mobs cleared is to turn your pet's taunt OFF so it doesn't pull the efreeti and say /PET KILL EFREETI.  Once they're in melee, turn the taunt back on.  This keeps the pet from doing some weird pathing and pulling the efreeti to a strange spot.  Even buffed, the efreeti will kill the pet if you don't help.<br>
<br>
The pet will also fight though the wall at the start.  Use this time to go around and annul and debuff the efreeti.  I'd recommend against Manastorm also.  Far too easy to do it within range.  Stick with 1 dot and a few nukes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uquaelgeist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quaelgeist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(10/12/02 10:05:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=393.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> bah, its uba easy, and nice camp, too. I solo there usualy, and I can kill ALL imps, which means I am not loosing any xp - and that solo... all you need is level 60, epic, and bob <p><center>
